## Summary

- Updates winston from 3.18.3 to 3.19.0
- Simplifies `closeLogger()` by removing timeout-based workaround

Winston 3.19.0 ([winstonjs/winston#2594](https://github.com/winstonjs/winston/pull/2594)) fixes issue [#1504](https://github.com/winstonjs/winston/issues/1504) where the File transport's `finish` event would fire before the actual file write completed. This was a long-standing bug since 2018 that caused log messages to be lost when calling `logger.end()` followed by `process.exit()`.

Previously, `closeLogger()` used a 100ms timeout as a workaround:
```typescript
await new Promise((resolve) => setTimeout(resolve, 100));
```

Now we can properly wait for the `finish` event:
```typescript
await Promise.all(
  fileTransports.map(
    (transport) =>
      new Promise<void>((resolve) => {
        transport.once('finish', resolve);
        transport.end();
      }),
  ),
);
```

This is more reliable and deterministic - no more arbitrary timeouts hoping the OS finishes writing.

Closes #6511

